<recipe>
    <name>Hurried-up Beanhole Beans</name>
    <indexCharacter>H</indexCharacter>
    <notes></notes>
    <servings>6</servings>
    <instructions>1. If using wood chips, soak in water to cover 1 hour before grilling; drain. Have ready a foil pan about 12 x 8 in. 

2. Heat outdoor grill for indirect grilling (see Indirect Grilling and Smoking, page 147) to medium (325°F to 350°F) as manufacturer directs. 

3. Meanwhile, heat a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Add bacon pieces and onion. Cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally, until bacon and onion are golden. Pour off all but 2 Tbsp fat. Stir in remaining ingredients; remove from heat. 

4. Put 2 slices bacon in foil pan. Add bean mixture; top with rest of bacon. 

5. Place pan in grill away from direct heat. Cover grill and cook 1 hour, or until beans are dark and thickened.

(If beans start to dry out, cover pan loosely with foil.)</instructions>
